  "examTip": "In a 5-stage pipeline (IF → ID → EX → MEM → WB), 7 instructions with 5 stages each would take 5 + (7-1) = 11 clock cycles instead of 7×5 = 35 cycles without pipelining. The speedup formula is: Speedup = (n × k) / (k + n - 1) where n = number of instructions and k = number of pipeline stages. Each instruction is staggered by 1 clock cycle, creating the characteristic staircase pattern.",
